'''Forbes's mannikin''' ('''''Lonchura forbesi''''') or the '''New Ireland munia''', is a species of [[estrildid finch]] breeding in [[Papua New Guinea]]. It has an estimated global extent of occurrence of {{convert|20,000|to|50,000|km2|abbr=on}}. It is found in subtropical or tropical lowland dry grassland habitat. The status of the species is evaluated as [[Least Concern]].

